    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303255">Figure 55.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303255" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303255.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Input Shaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If you only need to remove the mainshaft, you do not need to remove the input shaft.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six (6) retaining bolts from the input bearing cover, and remove the cover
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303256">(Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input bearing cover gasket and clean the gasket mounting surfaces on the cover
                and the main case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303256">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303256" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Clean Cover And Main Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If present, remove and discard the rubber seal ring on the input shaft. The ring is used
                only to seal the transmission during shipment.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the input shaft groove, remove the input bearing retaining snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a soft mallet, move the input shaft slightly rearward (approximately 1/16 inch) until
                resistance is felt.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grasp the input shaft and wiggle it. Pull it forward to move the input bearing forward to
                expose the snap ring on the outside of the input bearing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303257">(Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303257" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Expose Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The input shaft can be removed from the front of the case. Removal of the mainshaft is not
                    required.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a bearing puller tool and remove the input bearing from the case and input shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303258">(Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303258" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303258.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Remove Input Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring on the inside of the main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303259">Figure 59)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the main drive gear
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303259">(Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From inside the case, remove the main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303259">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303259" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303259.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 59. Remove Main Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
